<title type="html"><![CDATA[8/7(Sun.) Can we eat to starve cancer? / 3 Healthy Green Smoothies (Host: Gal)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=641&amp;p=666#p666"><![CDATA[
8/7(Sun.) Can we eat to starve cancer? / 3 Healthy Green Smoothies (Host: Gal)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:05 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:35 pm Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:35-9:00 pm Debate<br /><br />We will hold a zoom meeting only.<br /><br />Zoom meeting: Please click the link below<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ...<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br /><br />--------------------------------------------<br /><br />Session I: Can we eat to starve cancer?<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://tw.voicetube.com/videos/5237">https://tw.voicetube.com/videos/5237</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1. According to the speech, can we eat to starve cancer?<br />2. Do you have any idea about food synergy? (for example: the potent to combine two teas is better than either alone.)  <br />3. The speaker said the food of anti-angiogenesis like grape, soy, barsely, garlic, tomato, berries could also shrink fat.  Would you try to add these foods into your daily menu?<br />4. What is your opinion about &quot;what we eat is really our chemotherapy 3 times a day&quot;?<br /><br />---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />Session II: 3 Healthy Green Smoothies<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YGmQR8yCT_0">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YGmQR8yCT_0</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1. Have you ever made green smoothie or multigrain smoothie? If not, why?<br />2. Would you give green smoothie a try for the reason of immediate effect of drinking than eating?<br />3. If you have no choice but to drink it, would it be more acceptable if add soy bean, oat, warm water, etc into smoothie?<br />4. Do you have your own superfood and how does it benefit you?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=46353">Ellen Lu</a> — Mon Aug 01, 2022 8:25 pm</p><hr />
